snippet.textDisplay:
I got my kitty when she was 2 months old. We kept the litter box in my bathroom, so she used to go in there with me. The first week we had her, she followed me in there and the minute I lifted the lids, she jumped right in. She learned her lesson the first time, but if I hadn't been in there when it happened, she might not have had the opportunity for another try.


You gotta watch that toilet; make sure you keep the lid down. If they slip down too far in the bowl and can't pull out with their hind feet, they can't pull their front legs out of the drain hole and they can drown.
